title: "Narrow Scientific Model Safety Evaluation: A Framework for Dual-Use Risk Assessment in Protein Language Models"
authors:
  - family-names: "Kim"
    given-names: "JangKeun"
    orcid: "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-8733-9925"
    affiliation: "Weill Cornell Medicine"
    email: "jak4013@med.cornell.edu"
abstract: >-
  Empirical dual-use risk assessment framework for protein language models (ESM-2) and structure-based design tools (ProteinMPNN, EvoDiff, LigandMPNN). Introduces FSPE (Functional Site Prediction Entropy) and FSI (Functional Specificity Index) metrics with Physical Realizability Tier system decoupling computational risk from physical risk.
